result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler Nicholas Ingel-Lasch was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Tyler Nicholas Ingel-Lasch is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Tyler Nicholas Ingel-Lasch was found guilty of Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

1:44 PM Defendant Tyler Nicholas Ingel-Lasch appears in Court, Atty Liesl E. Nelson appeared via zoom, ADA Kaley Walker appears for the State of Wisconsin. Court notes DE has paid $19.90 in restitution.  ADA Walker: plea to Count 2 - costs ($443.00) and restitution $19.90, 10% restitution surcharge and dismiss Count 1. DE questions on payment reduction.  Court notes a Plea Questionnaire has not been completed.  Court informs Defendant of charges, possible penalties and constitutional rights.  Defendant understands charges, penalties and constitutional rights. Defendant pleas guilty to Ct#2. Counsel stipulates to factual basis.   Court finds def is making plea knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily and waives constitutional rights. Court finds a factual basis to accept the plea. Court finds Defendant guilty of Ct#2 and dismisses Count 1. ADA Walker addresses sentencing- joint recommendations, Victim rights are in compliance.  Atty Nelson agress; requests waiver of part of the costs or community service. Court orders:$267.00 court costs, 1 year to pay, $19.90 restitution, $1.90 surcharge, provide a DNA sample within 30 days.  Appeal rights are given to the defendant.
Status conference on June 30, 2022 at 01:45 pm.

ADA Walker is requesting a warrant. Court will authorize warrant and stay until next hearing, DE must appear in person and on time. Court adjourned at 4:06 pm.  Status conference scheduled for June 30, 2022 at 01:45 pm.
